The paper deals with fine-grained image search, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) for learning discriminative representations, which falls under the category of adversarial learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of an open-set scenario, which involves matching images from unseen and unknown categories, indicating the involvement of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-view images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of a neural network for learning representations suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
